text: Th is a digraph in the Latin alphabet, which is made of the consonant letters T and H. It is used in many Latin languages including English. == Languages == Some languages use the digraph Th like in “tháng” (month in Vietnamese), “thé” (tea in French) and “thing” in English. ==Related pages== *Ch (digraph) == References == Category:Latin alphabet
title: Th (digraph)
